### III. Senses & Definitions

**1. Primary Sense: Graphical Representation**
To scratch or draw lines on a surface; to delineate.
> **Pind. O. 6. 71:** **γράψεν** θέσει • *he incised/wrote it by decree.*
> [!NOTE] 
> Originally referred to the act of scratching on bark or tablets (cf. Mycenaean *ka-ra-wi*).

**2. Standard Sense: Writing**
To write, to compose, to record in writing.
- **2a.** To write a letter or document. (*epistolar*)
- **2b.** To register a name; to enroll for military service.
- **2c.** To propose a law (*v. mid.* **γράφομαι νόμον**).

**3. Judicial Sense (Attic Law)**
To bring an indictment against someone; to prosecute.
- **Usage:** **γράφεσθαί τινα γραφήν** • *to bring a public action against someone.*

